   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>Year 5-4 of our lords Diocletianus and Maximianus, Augusti, Epeiph 18. Ammonios, son of Papeeis, through Heron, son of Ammonas, (has paid) for the epibole of . . ., for the horiodeiktia of Karanis, four hundred drachmai, equal 400 drachmai. Through me, Horion</ab>
         </div>
